Title: 3+1 dimensional Yang-Mills theory as a local theory of evolution of
  metrics on 3 manifolds
Authors: Pushan Majumdar and H.S.Sharatchandra
Comments: 7 pages, revtex
Report-no: IMSc./2000/08/46
Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B491 (2000) 199-202
\\
  An explicit canonical transformation is constructed to relate the physical
subspace of Yang-Mills theory to the phase space of the ADM variables of
general relativity. This maps 3+1 dimensional Yang-Mills theory to local
evolution of metrics on 3 manifolds.
